  <!-- ── In-app manual ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       Markdown source files for HelpWindow plus their illustrative PNGs.
       Plain text — no preprocess. Outline lives in
       docs/manual-outline-v2.md (s128-locked: 11 chapters, 63 leaves).

       Image filename convention: chapter-prefix + [area-interest], where
       area is the surface (toolbar, layers, motif…) and interest is what
       the shot is highlighting on it. So 5-2-1-motif-section.png reads
       as "Motif page, the section view." Each leaf has one default slot
       pre-listed below; pages with multiple shots add more aliases when
       needed.

       Adding a topic:
         1. drop the .md in resources/help/
         2. add a <file> entry below
         3. append a row in HelpWindow::build_topic_list

       Adding a screenshot:
         1. drop the file in resources/help/img/ matching the alias
         2. move the opening of the comment past that line so it goes
            live (close the comment with a closing-marker on the previous
            line, restart the comment after the new live row)
         3. touch resources.xml; rebuild
         If you want a different slug than the placeholder, edit the
         alias and rename the PNG to match.

       The configure-time file(GLOB) in CMakeLists.txt picks new files
       up only on re-configure, but resources.xml mtime triggers the
       resource compile. Touching this file is the simplest way to
       force a rebundle. -->
